title: Claude review delegates should route around nested Claude session prohibition
---

Claude review delegates should route around nested Claude session prohibition

Delegating review/fix work to the Claude runner from within an active Claude Code session currently fails immediately with: "Claude Code cannot be launched inside another Claude Code session. Nested sessions share runtime resources and will crash all active sessions."

Acceptance criteria:
- Delegate/background routing detects when the current session cannot safely launch Claude Code recursively.
- In that situation, clawq either automatically uses a safe alternative runner/model for the requested review/fix task or launches Claude with an explicit supported bypass mechanism if that is safe and intended.
- The failure mode is surfaced clearly and does not waste long-lived review attempts.
